{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"tusdpid74e193jiojaxd4nn","title":"Go Programming","desc":"","updated":1705874784235,"created":1705840500833,"custom":{},"fname":"Kubernetes.Go Programming","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"Dendron"},"contentHash":"4c20deddd29a8940568c75c0569787ee","links":[],"anchors":{"go-programming-in-kubernetes":{"type":"header","text":"Go Programming In Kubernetes","value":"go-programming-in-kubernetes","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1},"introduction":{"type":"header","text":"Introduction","value":"introduction","line":9,"column":0,"depth":2},"working":{"type":"header","text":"Working","value":"working","line":12,"column":0,"depth":2},"control-plane":{"type":"header","text":"Control Plane","value":"control-plane","line":15,"column":0,"depth":2},"api":{"type":"header","text":"API","value":"api","line":24,"column":0,"depth":2},"cluster":{"type":"header","text":"Cluster","value":"cluster","line":25,"column":0,"depth":2},"openapi":{"type":"header","text":"OpenAPI","value":"openapi","line":28,"column":0,"depth":3}},"children":["xfctexp3l6yk3u2l1w37uwk"],"parent":"kvfgz9sv96p3uqosotptdgk","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"go-programming\">Go Programming<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#go-programming\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"go-programming-in-kubernetes\">Go Programming In Kubernetes<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#go-programming-in-kubernetes\"></a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"introduction\">Introduction<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#introduction\"></a></h2>\n<p>Kubernetes is a container orchestration tools which uses declarative method. Kubernetes has an API through which we can interact. It is a REST HTTP based API.</p>\n<h2 id=\"working\">Working<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#working\"></a></h2>\n<p>In the beginning of the chain, users declare a high level resources like Pods, Deployments etc. Once the resources are declared then the middle level component called controllers are activated to transfer them into low-levels Pods. Then the schedular distributes those resources in the nodes. Now the node agent deploys the Pod in the scheduled cluster.</p>\n<h2 id=\"control-plane\">Control Plane<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#control-plane\"></a></h2>\n<p>The control plane is the main brain of the kubernetes. It handles all the complexity of handling the declared resources in the cluster. It's main components are </p>\n<ol>\n<li>The API Server - This is the main gateway through which the communication to the cluster is done</li>\n<li>The etcd database - This is a database which stores the state of the cluster. Only accessible through API server.</li>\n<li>The controller manager - This manages the controllers which transforms the users declared resources to kubernetes low level components. The controller sync with the API to maintain the state of the resources.</li>\n<li>Schedular - It maintains the resource distribution in the nodes. It watches the api server for change</li>\n<li>Kubelet - Agent in each nodes. It manages workload specified to it's specific node after schedular schedules it. It watches the API server for any change in its node.</li>\n<li>Kube-Proxy - Agent to manage network. Runs on all nodes and watches the API server for any change</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"api\">API<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#api\"></a></h2>\n<h2 id=\"cluster\">Cluster<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#cluster\"></a></h2>\n<p>Creating a cluster for testing API code can be found at <a href=\"https://github.com/anityam/kubernetesGo\">kubernetesGo</a>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"openapi\">OpenAPI<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#openapi\"></a></h3>\n<p>Kubernetes uses the openAPI format to specify it REST API HTTP calls. To check</p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Children</strong>\n<ol>\n